full_text: We owe all those who serve the public’s safety a debt of gratitude too large to repay. As we remember these men and pray for two more, let us come together to support those they left behind, and continue to honor the selfless bravery their fellow firefighters exhibit every day.

We mourn the loss of these two incredible men with their families and communities. We stand with you and will do everything we can to ease your burden — a burden we all carry together.
To Zachary and Ivan we say thank you — PA will never forget what you did for all of us. For your service and sacrifice, you have earned our eternal gratitude and respect.

full_text: The #GOPTaxBill is bad policy. It is a giveaway to the uber-wealthy and corporations. I urge PA members of Congress to vote no and work on real tax reform that will benefit the middle class.

And let’s not forget that the #GOPTaxBill will increase the national deficit by $1.45 trillion in the next 10 yrs and will immediately trigger an automatic $25 billion cut to Medicare next year + $125 billion in cuts to farm subsidies, health prevention funds, and student loans.
The #GOPTaxBill repeals the #ACA mandate, which the @USCBO estimates will increase premiums by an additional 10% each year, and kick 500K Pennsylvanians off of their insurance. #GOPTaxBill

The #GOPTaxBill caps the State and Local Tax (SALT) deduction, which currently ensures that PA families won’t be taxed twice by the federal gov’t. This cap will increase the tax burden on PA homeowners by as much as $1600 per year.

The #GOPTaxBill raises the threshold to qualify for the estate tax, which benefits only the wealthiest 140 estates in PA. These estates, all worth >$22M, will see a tax cut of $4.4M. That revenue could be used to provide 1100 PA students Pell Grants to make college affordable.
More than half of the tax cuts in the #GOPTaxBill go to the top 1% while Pennsylvanians earning less than $75K will pay more in taxes by 2027. 713,000 of our constituents will see a tax hike by 2027.
Large corporations will see a permanent 14% tax cut in the #GOPTaxBill, while individuals making $40K will see a modest tax cut disappear by 2023.

I’m urging Pennsylvania’s Congressional delegation to vote against the #GOPTaxBill. In my letter to PA members, I highlighted what independent reviews have said for weeks: this bill prioritizes the wealthy over the middle class. https://t.co/XmYN6e5koo

For all these reasons, I have no confidence in this commission’s administration, standards of security, or its true intentions.

The commission’s request for states to email their entire files containing personal data flies in the face of basic privacy standards.

We have not provided Mr. Kobach, or the federal government, any authority to do this.
Statements by Vice Chair Kobach suggest his intent may be to improperly use PA’s data -- including sharing it in some public manner.
State law requires that it be used only for elections, political activities or law enforcement purposes.
…from tampering with or altering the list, or from further distributing the list to the public.
Now, any citizen can buy PA’s public voter file for a fee, but state law also prohibits anyone from using the list for improper purposes...

Such actions are not legitimately within the province of the commission.
Let me be very clear: indiscriminately kicking legitimate voters off voter rolls is a real assault on the integrity of our elections.

full_text: Here's my full letter to the Trump administration's Kris Kobach denying his request for personal information of every registered PA voter. https://t.co/ZKo8yqC11f
End of thread.
Voter suppression is undemocratic. I will not allow PA to participate in furthering the trend of suppression seen across the country.
The right to vote is absolute and I have no confidence that you seek to bolster - not hinder – it.
And I would support any effort to invest more federal funding in protecting our voter systems and improving voting technology.
I would be more interested in hearing from the White House how they are protecting our elections from illegal and international influence.
I have no interest in contributing to any effort to suppress the right to vote or create unnecessary or unfair burdens on voters.
Here in PA, a court of law has already struck down a voter identification program for putting undo burden on this fundamental right.
I also have grave concerns that this is the precipitous pretext for pursuing restrictions on the fundamental right of citizens to vote.
These attacks on Pennsylvania and the country’s most important democratic institution - voting - remain unproven.
Even worse, after the election the President-elect said millions of votes in U.S. had been cast illegally while providing no evidence.
During the campaign, then-candidate Trump repeatedly suggested wide-spread voter fraud in Pennsylvania without evidence.
I have serious reservations given historical suppression of voting rights and the Trump admin's false statements on the integrity of voting.
You can add PA to that list. We will not participate in this systematic effort to suppress the vote. https://t.co/EHnY2NJI5R
